{"id": "272302", "revid": "42014766", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=272302", "title": "Warbear Matriarch", "text": "The Warbear Matriarch is a &lt;a href=\"polar%20bear\"&gt;polar bear&lt;/a&gt; ridden by the player when competing in the &lt;a href=\"Pit%20of%20the%20Fang\"&gt;Pit of the Fang&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Brunnhildar%20Village\"&gt;Brunnhildar Village&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Storm%20Peaks\"&gt;Storm Peaks&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey are involved in the quests:\nUse.\nIn the quest \"The Warm-Up\", you beat up on a huge &lt;a href=\"Yeti\"&gt;Yeti&lt;/a&gt; that has been chained up nearby. If you find yourself in trouble, you can back out of range.\nIn the quests \"Into the Pit\" and \"Back to the Pit\", you find yourself facing (other) &lt;a href=\"Hyldnir\"&gt;Hyldnir&lt;/a&gt; on their own warbears. The &lt;a href=\"Pit%20of%20the%20Fang\"&gt;Pit of the Fang&lt;/a&gt; is a free-for-all among the warbear riders. You can as easily find yourself facing 3 at a time as you can attack another warbear while it is attacking a third warbear.\nUsing the \"Charge\" stuns the target for a moment, allowing you to get a few more hits in without getting thwacked in return. To achieve the minimum distance in the pit, you most often have to do the \"Smash\" first, then follow up with your charge. Mostly, the \"Maul\" ability will be used."}
