{"id": "76594", "revid": "40286752", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=76594", "title": "Warbucks", "text": "Warbucks.\nRyann, 01/04/2005\nStaying at the top spot in the new PvP honor system will not be easy. If you ever had to quit a raid on an enemy capital early because your frail human body forced you to bed, then you know what we mean. But fear not \u2013 a solution is at hand in the form of our new PvP honor bonus program called Warbucks, an exclusivity for our European players! \nWhen you vanquish another character in honorable PvP combat, the player dealing the finishing blow will be able to loot the corpse of his fallen enemy and pick up a special token called a \u201eWarbuck\u201d. All inns will have their own Buckmonger-NPC who will provide players with powerful coffee potions that will bestow extremely useful buffs when consumed in exchange for their hard-earned Warbucks. \nBut wait, that's not all! For each fifty Warbucks that you turn in you will receive a special reward. The Buckmonger will send you an in-game mail containing your exclusive Coffee Code. Using your Coffee Code, you will be able to claim a real medium-sized coffee of your choice at a participating caf\u00e9 near you (We will be providing a list of participating caf\u00e9s for each country on this site shortly). Not even sleep will be able to stop you now, thanks to Warbucks!"}
