{"id": "44071", "revid": "38791128", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44071", "title": "Explosive", "text": "An explosive is a &lt;a href=\"consumable\"&gt;consumable&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"device\"&gt;device&lt;/a&gt; that can cause &lt;a href=\"damage\"&gt;damage&lt;/a&gt; or other effects when used. While in-game only &lt;a href=\"Engineer\"&gt;Engineer&lt;/a&gt; players can use these weapons, many variants of &lt;a href=\"sapper\"&gt;sapper&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"bombardier\"&gt;bombardier&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mortar%20team\"&gt;mortar operator&lt;/a&gt; NPCs are known to use explosives in battle.\nBombs.\nA type of explosive only &lt;a href=\"Engineer\"&gt;Engineer&lt;/a&gt;s can &lt;a href=\"use\"&gt;use&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"craft\"&gt;craft&lt;/a&gt; that produces a Ground Targeted &lt;a href=\"Area%20of%20Effect\"&gt;Area of Effect&lt;/a&gt;. Like Grenades and Mortars, bombs typically have a secondary effect (&lt;a href=\"incapacitate\"&gt;incapacitate&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"silence%20effect\"&gt;silence&lt;/a&gt;) as well as damage. They cannot be used while moving. When bombs are &lt;a href=\"use\"&gt;use&lt;/a&gt;d, a green targetting symbol appears on the ground that can be moved around. The targetting symbol becomes a red 'no' symbol when moved out of range. After acquiring a valid target, click to throw the bomb. The table below summarizes the variety of bombs available to &lt;a href=\"Engineer\"&gt;Engineer&lt;/a&gt;s; &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; required and effects. The secondary effect is noted as unreliable above a certain level (the level limit, below).\nDynamite.\nA type of explosive only &lt;a href=\"Engineer\"&gt;Engineer&lt;/a&gt;s can &lt;a href=\"craft\"&gt;craft&lt;/a&gt; that produces a Ground Targeted &lt;a href=\"Area%20of%20Effect\"&gt;Area of Effect&lt;/a&gt;. When dynamite is &lt;a href=\"use\"&gt;use&lt;/a&gt;d, a green targetting symbol appears on the ground that can be moved around. The targetting symbol becomes a red 'no' symbol when moved out of range. After acquiring a valid target, click to throw the dynamite. The table below summarizes the variety of dynamite available; &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; required and effects.\nGrenades.\nA grenade is a type of &lt;a href=\"explosive\"&gt;explosive&lt;/a&gt; only &lt;a href=\"Engineer\"&gt;Engineer&lt;/a&gt;s can &lt;a href=\"craft\"&gt;craft&lt;/a&gt; that produces a Ground Targeted &lt;a href=\"Area%20of%20Effect\"&gt;Area of Effect&lt;/a&gt;. When grenades are &lt;a href=\"use\"&gt;use&lt;/a&gt;d, a green targetting symbol appears on the ground that can be moved around. The targetting symbol becomes a red \"no\" symbol when moved out of range. After acquiring a valid target, click to throw the grenade.\nLike &lt;a href=\"bomb\"&gt;bomb&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"mortar\"&gt;mortar&lt;/a&gt;s, grenades typically have a secondary effect\nin addition to the damage. Unlike bombs, grenades can be used while moving. \nThe table below summarizes the variety of grenades available;\n&lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; required and effects.\nMortars.\nA type of explosive only &lt;a href=\"Engineer\"&gt;Engineer&lt;/a&gt;s can &lt;a href=\"use\"&gt;use&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"craft\"&gt;craft&lt;/a&gt; that produces a Ground Targeted &lt;a href=\"Area%20of%20Effect\"&gt;Area of Effect&lt;/a&gt;. Like Bombs and Grenades, mortars have secondary effects. When mortars are &lt;a href=\"use\"&gt;use&lt;/a&gt;d, a green targetting symbol appears on the ground that can be moved around. The targetting symbol becomes a red 'no' symbol when moved out of range. After acquiring a valid target, click to fire the mortar. The table below summarizes the variety of mortars available to &lt;a href=\"Engineer\"&gt;Engineer&lt;/a&gt;s; &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; required and effects."}
