{"id": "565103", "revid": "40389549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=565103", "title": "Expulsom", "text": "Expulsom is a &lt;a href=\"Rare\"&gt;rare&lt;/a&gt; crafting reagent necessary for many high end \"\" profession recipes.\nSource.\nExpulsom can be obtained through several sources. Primarily, it is gained through &lt;a href=\"Scrapper\"&gt;scrapping&lt;/a&gt; \"Battle for Azeroth\" armor, weapons, and trinkets. Each weapon and armor item scrapped have a chance to grant one Expulsom, in addition to other crafting reagents. Trinkets (excluding crafted) will always yield 1 Expulsom, but no other crafting reagents. Crafted trinkets (via alchemy) will refund their Expulsom when scrapped, but will not yield any additional Expulsom. Expulsom cannot be obtained via &lt;a href=\"Enchanting%23Disenchanting\"&gt;disenchanting&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlchemy.\nExpulsom can be created with &lt;a href=\"Alchemy\"&gt;Alchemy&lt;/a&gt; (110) using Transmute: Expulsom; taught by the Kul Tiran and Zandalari alchemy trainers, &lt;a href=\"Clever%20Kumali\"&gt;Clever Kumali&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Elric%20Whalgrene\"&gt;Elric Whalgrene&lt;/a&gt; for . This transmute creates 5x Explosum but can only be performed once per day.\nEnchanting.\nExpulsom can be crafted with &lt;a href=\"Enchanting\"&gt;Enchanting&lt;/a&gt; (1) using the conversion, Sanguinated Expulsom; taught by the Kul Tiran and Zandalari enchanting trainers, &lt;a href=\"Emily%20Fairweather\"&gt;Emily Fairweather&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enchantress%20Quinni\"&gt;Enchantress Quinni&lt;/a&gt; for .\nQuesting.\nIn addition to the above sources, Expulsom is a potential reward from specific &lt;a href=\"world%20quest\"&gt;world quest&lt;/a&gt;s. The world quests that may reward them are either general turn-in quests (Supplies Needed), or profession restricted quests (Work Orders)"}
