{"id": "280835", "revid": "42014766", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=280835", "title": "General Grimaxe", "text": "General Grimaxe is the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Iron%20clan\"&gt;Dark Iron dwarves&lt;/a&gt; attacking the &lt;a href=\"Ironforge%20Airfield\"&gt;Ironforge Airfield&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Dun%20Morogh\"&gt;Dun Morogh&lt;/a&gt;. He can be seen riding a unique &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Iron%20Golem%20%28General%20Grimaxe%29\"&gt;Dark Iron Golem&lt;/a&gt; while attempting to rally his troops at the frozen lake south of the airfield.\nThough he worked under orders from &lt;a href=\"Ambassador%20Slaghammer\"&gt;Ambassador Slaghammer&lt;/a&gt;, a known &lt;a href=\"Twilight%27s%20Hammer\"&gt;Twilight's Hammer&lt;/a&gt; loyalist, it is unknown if Grimaxe himself and his forces were Hammer cultists as well.\nHe drops no loot and awards no &lt;a href=\"experience\"&gt;experience&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "351783", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=351783", "title": "General Hammond Clay", "text": "General Hammond Clay is the successor of the late General &lt;a href=\"Marcus%20Jonathan\"&gt;Marcus Jonathan&lt;/a&gt; as commander of the defense of &lt;a href=\"Stormwind%20City\"&gt;Stormwind City&lt;/a&gt;, following Jonathan's death during the &lt;a href=\"Attack%20on%20Theramore%20Isle\"&gt;Attack on Theramore Isle&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found at the end of the &lt;a href=\"Valley%20of%20Heroes\"&gt;Valley of Heroes&lt;/a&gt;, in front of the statue of &lt;a href=\"Turalyon\"&gt;Turalyon&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe also shows up with &lt;a href=\"High%20Sorcerer%20Andromath\"&gt;High Sorcerer Andromath&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Maginor%20Dumas\"&gt;Maginor Dumas&lt;/a&gt; to arrest &lt;a href=\"Hogger\"&gt;Hogger&lt;/a&gt;, as did his predecessor.\nHistory.\nMists of Pandaria.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"pandaren\"&gt;pandaren&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s entered Stormwind for the first time, Hammond welcomed them. After &lt;a href=\"Aysa%20Cloudsinger\"&gt;Aysa Cloudsinger&lt;/a&gt; asked for an audience with their \"emperor\" to join the &lt;a href=\"Alliance\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt;, he corrected her by mentioning that they would meet &lt;a href=\"Varian%20Wrynn\"&gt;King Varian Wrynn&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Stormwind%20Keep\"&gt;Stormwind Keep&lt;/a&gt;. As they left, he noticed &lt;a href=\"Jojo%20Ironbrow\"&gt;Jojo Ironbrow&lt;/a&gt;'s pillar and ordered them to behave well.\nLegion.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"third%20invasion%20of%20the%20Burning%20Legion\"&gt;third invasion of the Burning Legion&lt;/a&gt;, when the city was under lockdown because of the infiltration from the &lt;a href=\"Veiled%20Hand\"&gt;Veiled Hand&lt;/a&gt;, Hammond organized the soldiers on the bridge, inspected the smoke explosion in &lt;a href=\"Trade%20District\"&gt;Trade District&lt;/a&gt; and ultimately guarded the entrance of &lt;a href=\"Stormwind%20Keep\"&gt;Stormwind Keep&lt;/a&gt;.\nBattle for Azeroth.\nAt the time of the &lt;a href=\"Fourth%20War\"&gt;Fourth War&lt;/a&gt;, he participated in the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20for%20Lordaeron\"&gt;Battle for Lordaeron&lt;/a&gt;, escorting the &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt; through the &lt;a href=\"Lion%27s%20Wake\"&gt;Lion's Wake&lt;/a&gt; toward the &lt;a href=\"Ruins%20of%20Lordaeron\"&gt;Ruins of Lordaeron&lt;/a&gt;. Later, he was encountered by &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt; champions that attacked an Alliance host marching from &lt;a href=\"Stromgarde\"&gt;Stromgarde&lt;/a&gt; towards the ruins of &lt;a href=\"Durnholde%20Keep\"&gt;Durnholde Keep&lt;/a&gt;.\nDragonflight.\nAfter thwarting the rebellion of &lt;a href=\"Duncon%20Ratsbon\"&gt;Duncon Ratsbon&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Defias%20Brotherhood\"&gt;Defias Brotherhood&lt;/a&gt;, Hammond promoted the Stormwind champion into a Lionguard and bestowed them with new armor.\nRelatives.\nHe may be related to &lt;a href=\"Eula%20Clay\"&gt;Eula Clay&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "562511", "revid": "42014766", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=562511", "title": "General Harris", "text": "General Harris is a &lt;a href=\"Forsaken\"&gt;Forsaken&lt;/a&gt; located on board the &lt;a href=\"Seething%20Shore%20Horde%20gunship\"&gt;Horde gunship&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Seething%20Shore\"&gt;Seething Shore&lt;/a&gt;.\nRelatives.\nHe may be related to &lt;a href=\"Darla%20Harris\"&gt;Darla Harris&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chief%20Plaguebringer%20Harris\"&gt;Chief Plaguebringer Harris&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Oliver%20Harris\"&gt;Oliver Harris&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "309830", "revid": "42014766", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=309830", "title": "General Hawthorne", "text": "General John Hawthorne is the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Forward%20Command\"&gt;Forward Command&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Southern%20Barrens\"&gt;Southern Barrens&lt;/a&gt; and an Alliance &lt;a href=\"quest%20giver\"&gt;quest giver&lt;/a&gt;. \nHistory.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"scout\"&gt;scout&lt;/a&gt;s reported that Taurajo's most dangerous units were out on the hunt he ordered the sacking &lt;a href=\"Camp%20Taurajo\"&gt;Camp Taurajo&lt;/a&gt;, despite it being a 'soft target' he recognized that the camp had been used to recruit, equip, and train Horde infantry for many years. During the attack he ordered his men to leave a gap open in the line so the citizens of Taurajo may escape, and despite this some &lt;a href=\"Yonada\"&gt;civilian&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Krulmoo%20Fullmoon\"&gt;casualties&lt;/a&gt; did occur. Hawthorne also ordered Wildhammer mercenaries to firebomb the village. Following this there are those in the &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt; that refers to Hawthorne as the \"The Butcher of Taurajo\" due to his actions being perceived as the intentional killing of civilians.\nThere are those that ended up in his ranks who are non-violent criminals recruited from the &lt;a href=\"Stormwind%20Stockades\"&gt;Stormwind Stockades&lt;/a&gt;, following Alliance policy. He discovered that some had broke ranks to loot the ruins, which among other things, he considered disrespectful. He had an adventurer arrest several; others witnessed this and crawled back to him, requesting clemency. He had them thrown into the brig at &lt;a href=\"Northwatch%20Hold\"&gt;Northwatch Hold&lt;/a&gt; to let them stew for a bit.\nAfter some initial interactions with the &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;, he sends them off to &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Triumph\"&gt;Fort Triumph&lt;/a&gt; and says he will travel there himself separately. After this, he is killed in the Horde quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Butcher%20of%20Taurajo\"&gt;The Butcher of Taurajo&lt;/a&gt;. His corpse was later retrieved and is found in &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Triumph\"&gt;Fort Triumph&lt;/a&gt;, being mourned by his widowed wife, &lt;a href=\"Clarice%20Hawthorne\"&gt;Clarice Hawthorne&lt;/a&gt;.\nHigh Chieftain of the tauren, &lt;a href=\"Baine%20Bloodhoof\"&gt;Baine Bloodhoof&lt;/a&gt;, believed that Camp Taurajo was a legitimate military target and Hawthorne carried out the attack best he could.\nQuotes.\nI want you to know that I sincerely appreciate your aid, &lt;class&gt;. We are not fighting beasts out here, but a foe both cunning and fanatical. We must stick together or hang separately.\nAny savage can win a war. The true hero aims not merely for victory on the battlefield, but to attain a lasting peace after the final arrow falls.\nYou're doing incredible work here in the Barrens, &lt;name&gt;.\nWith the help of heroes like you, we can secure Kalimdor, and in doing so ensure a lasting peace in our homelands.\nSpeculation.\nConsidering he wears the Theramore Tabard, and his wife says that she came to the Barrens from Theramore, they may have been citizens of Theramore."}
{"id": "288213", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=288213", "title": "General Husam", "text": "General Husam is a boss of the &lt;a href=\"Lost%20City%20of%20the%20Tol%27vir\"&gt;Lost City of the Tol'vir&lt;/a&gt;. \nBackground.\nGeneral Husam is one of the &lt;a href=\"tol%27vir\"&gt;tol'vir&lt;/a&gt; that was granted his stone form back.\nDungeon Jornal.\n\"The &lt;a href=\"titan\"&gt;titan&lt;/a&gt;s themselves appointed General Husam as one of Uldum's foremost guardians. After &lt;a href=\"Siamat\"&gt;Siamat&lt;/a&gt;, Lord of the South Wind, cured the Neferset tol'vir's curse of flesh, Husam helmed a rebellion that culminated in the air elemental's imprisonment.\"\nStrategy.\nHeroic\nOn heroic, Husam spawns too many traps on the ground around him to safely fight him in one place. Because of this, the tank should kite the boss around the arena to keep the number of traps endangering the party members to a minimum. His shockwaves, the traps, and his Bad Intentions throw will make the battlefield dangerous quickly and the party members need to be quick to react. \nIn Hearthstone.\nHusam appears as that can be encountered in the adventure in the \"\" expansion for \"&lt;a href=\"Hearthstone%20%28game%29\"&gt;Hearthstone&lt;/a&gt;\".\nVideos.\n&lt;vplayer /&gt;"}
{"id": "643908", "revid": "40389549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=643908", "title": "General Huxzar", "text": "General Huxzar is a &lt;a href=\"night%20elf\"&gt;night elf&lt;/a&gt; who served &lt;a href=\"Queen%20Azshara\"&gt;Queen Azshara&lt;/a&gt; and killed &lt;a href=\"Professor%20Elryna\"&gt;Professor Elryna&lt;/a&gt; when she showed him her research on the creation of &lt;a href=\"snapdragon\"&gt;snapdragon&lt;/a&gt;s. His subsequent fate is unknown.\nThe vision of this event was discovered by &lt;a href=\"Collector%20Kojo\"&gt;Collector Kojo&lt;/a&gt; and an &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Nar%27anan\"&gt;Nar'anan&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Nazjatar\"&gt;Nazjatar&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "560834", "revid": "42014766", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=560834", "title": "General Jakra'zet", "text": "General Jakra'zet is a &lt;a href=\"sand%20troll\"&gt;sand troll&lt;/a&gt; member of the &lt;a href=\"Zanchuli%20Council\"&gt;Zanchuli Council&lt;/a&gt;. He earned his place after the &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt; crushed &lt;a href=\"Farraki%20tribe\"&gt;his people&lt;/a&gt; to dust, and so he does not like them.\nBackground.\nA decorated &lt;a href=\"Sandfury%20tribe\"&gt;Sandfury&lt;/a&gt; soldier, Jakra'zet joined the coalition of forces under the banner of the &lt;a href=\"Prophet%20Zul\"&gt;Prophet Zul&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Pandaria\"&gt;Pandaria&lt;/a&gt; campaign. Despite the outcome of the campaign, Jakra'zet's skill in strategy and tactics could not be denied. Eventually, the great Prophet Zul petitioned to promote Jakra'zet to the role of general. Of the Zanchuli Council, &lt;a href=\"Yazma\"&gt;Yazma&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Vol%27kaal\"&gt;Vol'kaal&lt;/a&gt; voted with Zul for the appointment. &lt;a href=\"Hexlord%20Raal\"&gt;Raal&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wardruid%20Loti\"&gt;Loti&lt;/a&gt; objected, but they were overruled by &lt;a href=\"Rastakhan\"&gt;King Rastakhan&lt;/a&gt;, who was curious at what Jakra'zet could accomplish. And thus, Jakra'zet became the first of the Sandfury Tribe to hold the rank of General of the Zandalari army. Jakra'zet holds a great hatred for the &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt;, holding them responsible for the Sandfury tribe's downfall. He counselled against Rastakhan granting the Horde a place of honor within Zuldazar, eager instead to execute their representative himself, but was overruled.\n&lt;a href=\"Princess%20Talanji\"&gt;Princess Talanji&lt;/a&gt; suspected that Jakra'zet plotted something in the deserts of &lt;a href=\"Vol%27dun\"&gt;Vol'dun&lt;/a&gt;. Jakra'zet oversaw the exile of many Zandalari to Vol'dun, including his personal chef, &lt;a href=\"Sezahjin\"&gt;Sezahjin&lt;/a&gt;, who was banished to the desert for cooking a meal that made the general ill. Jakra'zet also exiled any trolls who questioned his actions, including &lt;a href=\"Warguard%20Rakera\"&gt;Warguard Rakera&lt;/a&gt;, who came close to proving that Jakra'zet was a traitor to the crown. The general subsequently also hired &lt;a href=\"Grozztok%20the%20Blackheart\"&gt;Grozztok the Blackheart&lt;/a&gt; and sent assassins to the desert in order to slaughter the exiles. Those who distrusted the general were justified: in truth, Jakra'zet and his Sandfury trolls had struck up an alliance with the &lt;a href=\"Faithless\"&gt;Faithless&lt;/a&gt; emperor &lt;a href=\"Emperor%20Korthek\"&gt;Korthek&lt;/a&gt;, and together they plotted to unleash the &lt;a href=\"C%27Thrax\"&gt;C'Thrax&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Mythrax\"&gt;Mythrax the Unraveler&lt;/a&gt; from his tomb of &lt;a href=\"Atul%27Aman\"&gt;Atul'Aman&lt;/a&gt; and use him as a weapon to conquer Zandalar and, eventually, all of &lt;a href=\"Azeroth\"&gt;Azeroth&lt;/a&gt;. However, they first had to obtain the three keystones required to break the magical barrier around Atul'Aman.\nBefore long, Warguard Rakera's subordinate &lt;a href=\"Bladeguard%20Kaja\"&gt;Bladeguard Kaja&lt;/a&gt; and her companions \u2014 including the Horde &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt; \u2014 ventured into Vol'dun to search for Rakera. At the time, Jakra'zet was conversing with Emperor Korthek, telling him that they needed to speed things up as King Rastakhan had received \"nosey visitors\". When Jakra'zet noticed the &lt;a href=\"pterrordax\"&gt;pterrordax&lt;/a&gt; mounts of Kaja and her companions passing overhead, Korthek conjured lightning magic that blasted two of the intruders from the sky.\nLater, the adventurer encountered Jakra'zet and Grozztok at Atul'Aman, where they were apparently trying to find a way into the pyramid. When Jakra'zet noticed the trespasser, he ordered Grozztok to kill them and then teleported away.\nEventually, the adventurer, Kaja, and Rakera retrieved one of the three keystones and found allies in the form of a &lt;a href=\"Devoted\"&gt;group of sethrak&lt;/a&gt; led by &lt;a href=\"Vorrik\"&gt;Vorrik&lt;/a&gt;, who held another of the keys. While Kaja and Rakera stayed behind to guard the two keystones at the &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary%20of%20the%20Devoted\"&gt;Sanctuary of the Devoted&lt;/a&gt;, the adventurer worked with Vorrik and Vol'dun's &lt;a href=\"vulpera\"&gt;vulpera&lt;/a&gt; to assault the Faithless sethrak's stronghold and eventually kill Emperor Korthek himself. Meanwhile, however, Jakra'zet \u2014 who had already been given Korthek's key \u2014 assaulted the Sanctuary of the Devoted and stole the remaining two keystones, meaning that he now had everything he needed to break the seal on Atul'Aman. Kaja and Rakera hurried after the general into the great pyramid to prevent him from resurrecting Mythrax and were soon joined by Vorrik and the adventurer. Together, the four went to confront Jakra'zet at the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Font\"&gt;Blood Font&lt;/a&gt;, where he was in the process of conducting &lt;a href=\"Blood%20magic\"&gt;a blood ritual&lt;/a&gt; to raise Mythrax from the dead. During the battle, Jakra'zet incapacitated one of the adventurer's companions after the other, but was eventually mortally wounded by the hero. Rakera told Kaja to give the general a clean death, but before she had a chance to do so, a triumphant Jakra'zet jumped into the nearby pit, killing himself and thus performing the final blood sacrifice needed to resurrect Mythrax.\nQuotes.\nGossip.\nI don't care what deal ya think to barter from da King and his daughter. Know that ya not welcome in Zuldazar.\nAnd while da Princess may have a lot of authority, she not be queen yet.\nUntil then, da real power of Zuldazar lay with me and da Zanchuli Council.\nSpeculation.\nJakra'zet says that the &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt; laid waste to his people. This could refer to potential adventurers of the Horde who might have raided either &lt;a href=\"Zul%27Farrak\"&gt;Zul'Farrak&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Throne%20of%20Thunder\"&gt;Throne of Thunder&lt;/a&gt;."}
